interactions.flavorLineOne: Eva is glad to see you. She congratulates your contributions to the defense of the City, then tells you that this year's Solstice is special—Ikora, along with a small group of Warlocks, have come up with an unusual surprise… but she's not spilling the secret. You'll have to go see for yourself.

You tell Eva about your meditation. She nods. "The greatest thing we can do to honor those we've lost is to live well and be our best selves. Take that armor. Go out into the world. Reforge it. Make it into a symbol of something strong and proud and beautiful."

Eva seems relieved that you've returned safely from the Haunted Forest.

"I heard what the Spider asked you to do, and during the Festival of the Lost of all times!" Eva scowls. "I don't appreciate being manipulated into putting a Guardian at risk for some Glimmer or whatever treasure he had you hunting, but at least it ended well. Here, let me give you a little something extra for all your trouble."

"And if nothing else good comes of this, I learned a valuable lesson about dealing with the Spider…"

"Don't."

"Ominous tidings for the festival this year, aren't they?" Eva asks with subtle tension. She smiles through it, wearing a mask of quiet confidence.

"Why don't you try on a mask, join in the festivities? We can all find a little strength in them.

"And… normally I'd leave it at that, but we received a rather generous shipment of essential supplies for the festival from—of all people—the Spider, that scoundrel baron of the Tangled Shore. Keeping in line with his reputation, he called it an investment rather than a gift.

"The Spider's asked for a favor in return, but he said he'd only relay it to his… favorite associate. Would you be a dear and see what it is he wants? I think it's best for everyone if we stay on his good side."

"Welcome, welcome!" Eva says with a smile, though it's clear the normal cheer in her eyes is somewhat diminished. "An auspicious start to the festival this year, isn't it? But what time is more important to remember those who have passed than in the face of impending loss? The sacrifices of those who came before allow us to be here today, making it all the more important that we acknowledge them."

"I know it's… beyond belief out there. I know people are scared. But fear is normal; fear is a human reaction. You can be afraid and still be brave. That's part of what the masks of the festival show us. We can be strong on the outside, even if we're frightened within."
"Excellent work, dear," Eva says. "You've shown great spirit during the Games. I hope this little reward will help you remember them all year."
"Very impressive," Eva says with a smile. "You've earned this. Please choose your favorite. If you keep up this enthusiasm, perhaps you'll earn another next week."

"Well done, my friend!" Eva says. "I had these made so that Guardians of all kinds could show their appreciation for one another. Choose your favorite, and if you show the same spirit next week, you can earn another."

"Did Zavala like his gift?" Eva asks, and then laughs. "Whether he said so or not, I assure you he did."

She smiles. "Go on, then. Spread some cheer. You'll discover even more ingredients and recipes on your travels. I'm sure you'll find what you need to make gifts for everyone on your list."

The Festival of the Lost is nearing its end. Be sure to collect any remaining masks and participate in all associated activities this week!

Happy Festival of the Lost!

interactions.flavorLineOne: "A gift need not be material. Sometimes your presence, a little favor, or some advice is just as welcome. The Dawning is a time to care for one another." —Eva Levante

"Well done, dear," Eva says with a warm smile. "You are a perfect example of the Guardian Games spirit. And you've made your class proud." She gives you a gift to thank you for all your work. "Keep enjoying the Games."

Eva is delighted to see the completed blueprint. She thanks you for your hard work and rewards you with a festive sparrow.

"I'm sure this will help you show off your Dawning spirit," she says warmly.
"The Revelry honors you and everything you do, Guardian. Celebrate it however you want. The Vanguard has helped me put together a festival across the solar system." —Eva Levante
Your voice is unleashed.
"Make your way to the Verdant Forest! The Vanguard and Osiris have prepared a celebration just for you." —Eva Levante
Welcome to the Revelry, Guardian. Here's a little pick-me-up to help your celebration along.

"Isn't it a marvelous idea!" Eva exclaims as you approach. "An island in the sky. My goodness. When I was a little girl, I read stories about such things, but you Guardians can actually make them real."

She sighs, sobering as she offers you a gift: a set of ruined armor from the Red War. "But of course, the Solstice is more than just floating islands. Take this armor to the Statue of Heroes, dear. Try to think about everyone who came before you, everyone who made it possible to stand here in this Tower today…"

"You're ready to start the Games, Guardian," Eva says. "I will have medal challenges for you every day. These challenges will allow you to support your class in the Games. Every medal you deposit at the Guardian Games podium will improve your class's daily standing."

She smiles. "Good luck, Guardian. Make your class proud. And have fun."

"Welcome to the Dawning, Guardian," Eva says. "At this time of year, the City joins together to celebrate and give thanks for all we have."

She smiles. "Last year, I asked Guardians to bake gifts for their friends using my Holiday Oven. I've improved the oven since then, and I would love to lend it to you again. I think you should begin by baking a gift for our dear Commander Zavala."
Eva Levante has transformed the Tower once again. She invites you to take part in a new City tradition: the Guardian Games.

"What a terrific effort you Warlocks made yesterday!" Eva says. "Silver looks good on you. But I see the fire in your eyes—you want the gold!"

She laughs. "Don't give up, my friend. Please take this reward for all of your efforts so far. Let it inspire you as you move forward."
Eva beams with pride. "Well done, my dear. That kind of work ethic will carry you through your whole life… let alone the summer! Ha!"
Eva encourages you to speak to Zavala about the Guardian Games. He can help get you started.

"Congratulations, my friend!" Eva says, beaming. "The Warlock banner rose to the top yesterday, bringing your team one step closer to the Guardian Games Cup."

She hands you a reward for your contributions. "Take this reward for your excellent work. And don't let up—the Hunters and Titans won't!"

"You are doing your team proud, my dear," Eva says. "Even in adversity, you Warlocks show us all how to be resolute in our goals. Perhaps today will be your day."

She hands you a reward for your contributions. "Take this reward for your part in yesterday's competition. Well done, and don't give up."

"Isn't the Guardian Games podium lovely?" Eva asks. "Many people in the Tower came together to create it. That is where we will track the progress of your class across the event. The class banners will rise and fall depending on your place in the competition."

She smiles. "Even the Drifter took part. He was kind enough to donate his deposit technology. It only took a little convincing." She hands you a medal. "Bring this to him, and he will register your new class item. Then you can deposit this medal and begin the Games."

"You are doing your team proud, my dear," Eva says. "Even in adversity, you Titans show us all how to stand strong. Perhaps today will be your day."

She hands you a reward for your contributions. "Take this reward for your part in yesterday's competition. Well done, and don't give up."

"I've set up a little challenge for you Guardians," Eva says. "The rewards are three handsome Ghost Shells to allow you and your Ghost to remember the Games all year long. Play hard each week and you can earn all three."
